  "prompt": "You push backward against the ground to move a skateboard forward. The force you make acts against the ground. What force acts against you to move you forward?",
  "response": "When you push backward against the ground with the skateboard, you are applying a force to the ground. According to Newton's third law of motion, for every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction. Therefore, the ground responds by exerting an equal and opposite force back on you. \n\nThis reaction force from the ground is what propels you\u2014and the skateboard\u2014forward. Essentially, as you push backward with your feet, the ground pushes you forward, allowing the skateboard to move in the forward direction. This interaction is a good illustration of action and reaction forces in action.",
